{
  "stem": "1895.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Polish-born Jews were being booted out of Germany, their possessions confiscated, and sent to Zbaszyn, a Polish-German border town. 'America was in a deep economic depression then, politically isolationist, with Nazis marching in the streets under swastika banners.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I discussed all those events with my father, but he was an optimist. 'Things always look darkest before dawn,' he said. 'Jewish people have had to endure Hamans throughout history, and somehow we survive.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hitler is just another Haman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He will exact a toll, but in the long run, we will persevere.'",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'And I said, 'But Father, why is the whole world against us?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why is there so much hatred?'",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'Can't we do something to defend ourselves?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And why, I ask, can we not leave-- --this godforsaken place full of hatred and bigotry?' 'When barraged with such questions, he would pet my head, and his eyes would become sad. 'To leave now would require a lot of money, which we don't have.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Besides, how can we leave our place of birth, where everyone knows us, our friends, our relatives?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The little we have sustains us here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it is more than we can hold in a new country in these times of world economic depression.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No, my son,' he said. 'Our strength is in our faith and in our Bible.' '",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "' 'Our strength is in our faith and in our Bible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We are the people of the book, even though sometimes that is not enough.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That is why we're trying to establish a state in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If not in my lifetime, then perhaps in yours, that will become a reality.' ' [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] That was the conversation.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
